body:
I would love to see us to explore storing each DataColumnSidecar separately as specified in @wemeetagain comment https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/pull/7947#discussion_r2159141837

instead of this non-spec wrapper
```typescript
export const dataColumnSidecarsDbWrapperSsz = new ContainerType(
  {
    blockRoot: ssz.Root,
    slot: ssz.Slot,
    dataColumnsLen: ssz.Uint8,
    dataColumnsSize: ssz.UintNum64,
    // // each byte[i] tells what index (1 based) the column i is stored, 0 means not custodied
    // max value to represent will be 128 which can be represented in a byte
    dataColumnsIndex: new ByteVectorType(NUMBER_OF_COLUMNS),
    dataColumnSidecars: ssz.fulu.DataColumnSidecars,
  },
  {typeName: "DataColumnSidecarsWrapper", jsonCase: "eth2"}
);
```

it simplifies a lot of thing: to store, to query and backfilling

_Originally posted by @twoeths in https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/pull/7947#pullrequestreview-3078551915_
